# Sort Module - Allocation-Free Sorting for Baremetal
#
# Provides in-place sorting and binary search suitable for bare-metal targets.
# No heap allocation. Operates on caller-supplied array slices.
#
# Public API:
#   - use std.sort.{bm_insertion_sort}   # Small / nearly-sorted arrays
#   - use std.sort.{bm_heapsort}         # General O(n log n), worst-case safe
#   - use std.sort.{bm_binary_search}    # O(log n) search in sorted array

# All functions exported from mod.spl are automatically available.
